 Day 113 Lockdown. Her container clutched tightly under her arm, experience has taught this young woman that when hand sanitiser is sprayed outdoors and there’s a breeze, it’s best to shut your eyes. On Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays the Southern Hills CAN group provides a hot meal to about 170 children and 60 adults who wait patiently for them to arrive. This photo is part of a series on Cape Town under lockdown.